<TITLE>School to carry out drugs tests on pupils over concerns about the 'party scene'</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Pupils at a school in Long Eaton will be asked to take drugs tests as part of the school's plans to crack down on illegal substances.

Trent College, on Derby Road, sent letters out to parents about its new school policy and invited them to an 'information evening' about drugs awareness.

The letter states that the session related to "current concerns regarding smoking and drugs" and that it would be "introducing random drugs testing for pupils in Years 10 and above".

